{{#> layouts/simple }}

  {{> navbar}}

  {{#> hero title='<span class="fw-bold text-primary">Donate</span> or Recycle'}}
    <p class="lead mb-4">
      <span class="fw-semibold">{{siteMetadata.name}}</span> is committed to the environmentally friendly recycling of e-waste.
      However, due to logistical reasons, we are unfortunately unable to accept all donations. Please see below for more details.
    </p>
  {{/hero}}

  <section class="container py-1">

    <!-- Personal / Single Donations -->
    <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3 fw-bold">Personal / Single Donations</h2>

    <p class="mb-3">
      We accept <span class="fw-medium">clean</span> (not damaged) laptops and tablets
      <span class="fw-bold">suitable for refurbishment</span> and reuse. However, we cannot accept:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-4">
      <li class="list-group-item">Printers or Scanners</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">Desktop Computers <sup>*</sup></li>
      <li class="list-group-item">Monitors / Screens<sup>*</sup></li>
      <li class="list-group-item">Digital Media</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">Miscellaneous Cables</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">DVD Players and Other Electronic Devices</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="mb-3">
      These items should be taken directly to a waste transfer station for responsible recycling.
      There is generally no charge for household electronic waste recycling.
      You can find more information on nearby recycling / eWaste centres and resources at:
    </p>

    <ul class="mb-4">
      <li><a href="#">Recycling Near You</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">TechCollect</a></li>
    </ul>

    <p class="mb-3">
      Disposal of <span class="fw-semibold">eWaste in landfill will be banned from July 2019</span> in {{site.address.addressRegion}}.
      However, eWaste is still able to be recycled for no charge at designated points across {{site.address.addressCountry}}.
      For more information on this change, please see
      <a href="https://www.sustainability.vic.gov.au/You-and-Your-Home/Waste-and-recycling/Household-waste/eWaste"
         target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Sustainability {{site.address.addressRegion}}: eWaste
      </a>.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      <sup>*</sup> Some exceptions do apply. Please contact us if you believe your computer or monitor is suitable for donation
      or if you have any questions (see tips below).
    </p>

    <!-- Business / Bulk Donations -->
    <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3 fw-bold">Business / Bulk Donations</h2>

    <p class="mb-3">
      <span class="fw-semibold">{{siteMetadata.name}}</span> is happy to accept bulk donations of laptops, desktops, and monitors from your business or school.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Depending on the quantity and distance, we can organise to retrieve these items from your location.
      If you are considering making a bulk donation, please contact us.
    </p>

    <!-- Tips Section -->
    <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3 fw-bold">Tips</h2>

    <p class="mb-3">
      If you are contacting us about a potential donation, it would be greatly appreciated if you could include the following information
      to help us assess if your computer can be given a second life:
    </p>

    <ul class="mb-5">
      <li>Original Operating System: (E.g. Windows XP, Windows 7)</li>
      <li>Computer Age: (E.g. 4 Years)</li>
      <li>CPU: (E.g. Core i3 2.8 GHz or AMD FX-4300 3.2 GHz)</li>
      <li>RAM: (E.g. 8 GB)</li>
      <li>Hard Drive Size: (E.g. 250 GB)</li>
    </ul>

  </section>

{{/layouts/simple}}